task.summary: Created IPlayable interface with play method. Created Guitar class that implements IPlayable.
Created Piano class that implements IPlayable. It has various specific properties for Piano and getters for these.
Introduced new instrument package and moved instrument type classes into this package. IDE refactored other classes to reflect this new package.

Created abstract class Instrument which implements IPlayable interface.
Created InstrumentType ENUM for the category of instrument e.g. string, woodwind etc
Created ISell interface which specifies a calaculateMarkup method to be used with Items to work out the markup.

Created Item abstract class at the top of the hierarchy of stock items. This implements the ISell interface and the calculateMarkup method to return the markup based on the difference between retail and wholesale prices.
Created new package for accessories inside the Item package. Created new GuitarString class which in an instance of accessories.

Added Accessory class which extends item. This is to hold shared behaviour for non instrument items sold by the shop.
Added DrumStick and GuitarString classes that extends Accessory.
Added shop package and moved item and all its sub packages inside this. IDE refactoring to achieve this. Many files moved.
Added AccessoryType ENUM to represent the categories of accessory available. Refactored the existing code to use this enum in place of a string.
Added calculateTotalPotentialProfit method to Shop class. This calls calculateMarkup for each item in the stock collection to get the total potential profit for all items in stock.
Added getStockItems to Shop class which returns a list of Items from the stock list so that further item details can be retrieved about the ISell objects in the stock list.
